<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-04-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-04-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="1066" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1066">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.11/3746.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Hamm</persName> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Durango</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-04-23">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 23, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Federal authorities refuse to allow me to send messages in code to
                            Secretary of State, acting under orders of military headquarters,
                            Torreon. Have also not received any messages from Washington for several
                            days. Hundred twenty Americans in this Consular District as follows:
                            sixty, Torreon; thirty Durango; and thirty scattering. About one half
                            will leave immediately. Please advise if this message received.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hamm</hi></signed>.</closer>
                        <pb facs="0789" n="673" xml:id="pg_673"/>
                        <frus:attachment>
                            <p rend="center">
                                <hi rend="italic">Act of Congress for Relief of Americans in
                                    Mexico</hi>.</p>
                            <p rend="flushleft">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Chap</hi>. 68.—An Act Providing an
                                appropriation for the relief and transportation of American citizens
                                in Mexico.</p>
                            <p>
                                <hi rend="italic">Be in enacted by the Senate and House of
                                    Representatives of the United States of America in Congress
                                    assembled</hi>, That for the relief of American citizens in
                                Mexico, including transportation to their homes in the United
                                States, there is appropriated, out of any money in the Treasury not
                                otherwise appropriated, the sum of $500,000, to be expended at the
                                discretion of the President.</p>
                            <closer><dateline rendition="#left">Approved, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-04-24">April 24, 1914</date>.</dateline></closer>
                        </frus:attachment>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>